        <div id="dsq-comment-header-43525" class="dsq-comment-header">
            <cite id="dsq-cite-43525">
                <span id="dsq-author-user-43525">Lee Johnson</span>
            </cite>
        </div>
        <div id="dsq-comment-body-43525" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-43525" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>I think we&#8217;ve been in the midst of it since 1994. I was out of the country from 1993 to 1995. The country I left was not the one I returned to. It was nascent in 95, but you could tell everything was different, forever. It was just a question of time. The Internet of things is an outgrowth of the digital revolution, and yes, we&#8217;re getting hammered in wave after wave of change. The Industrial Revolution went coal/steam, gasoline, electricity, television, electronics, each wave bringing about dramatic change. The digital revolution goes PC, Internet, e-business, Internet of things/3D printing.</p>
<p>We&#8217;re heading into an unknown area. I have adapted and adapted in my  life &#8230; but now I feel that I&#8217;ve gotten run over, the wave has passed over me, and I&#8217;m just churning in the debris afterward. I&#8217;m only 50. It must be exciting to be young &#8230;</p>
</div>
        </div>

